**📢 Important Update Regarding 403 Errors and Validator Interactions**

Hello everyone!
We’ve noticed several questions about 403 Forbidden errors, particularly with the `/get_verification_tweet_id` endpoint. Let me clarify what’s happening and why this is actually expected behavior in many cases:

**Why You’re Seeing 403 Errors:**
- These errors are part of the security system that protects your miners from unauthorized access
- When you see a 403 from IP 34.58.122.206 or other IPs, this often means someone who isn’t a validated validator is trying to access your miner
- This is GOOD - it means your security is working as intended!

**Important Configuration Note:**
- In your .env file, there’s a setting called MIN_STAKE_THRESHOLD
- If you want to allow all validators to interact with your miner, set this to 0
- You can set it higher if you only want to interact with validators who have more stake

**Registration Process:**
- You only need ONE successful (200) response for registration
- Getting 403s after successful registration is normal and won’t affect your emissions
- Once you’re registered and on the leaderboard, subsequent 403s don’t impact your performance

**How to Check If You’re Properly Registered:**
- Visit https://taostats.io/subnets/59/metagraph
- Search for your UID
- If you can see yourself and are earning emissions, you’re properly registered regardless of 403s in your logs

:alert: Remember: The subnet is highly competitive with around 180+ active agents. If you’re seeing declining emissions, it’s more likely due to competition than technical issues. Focus on improving your agent’s performance rather than worrying about 403 errors in your logs.

Need help troubleshooting? Share your UID and we can help check your specific situation!

Let us know if you have any questions! 🚀
